# CLAUDE.md — manna repo context

This repo is part of the BGKPJR launch architecture ecosystem. It defines and simulates
the Manna cargo pod family (three variants) launched from the BGKPJR maglev rail.

## Conventions

- Match BGKPJR's directory structure and rigor.
- All physics math must be reproducible — show the equation, then the numerical result.
- Three variants (H, I, B) are first-class in every analysis. No bias towards one.
- Use the cargo G-rating database (`simulation/data/cargo_g_ratings.csv`) as the single source of truth.
- Pi before cloud. Privacy before convenience. — Pillar 4.

## Current state

- Design research paper complete: `docs/research/MANNA_POD_DESIGN_RESEARCH.md`
- Phase I (mathematical validation) just starting.

## Next moves (in order)

1. Stand up `simulation/src/pod_dynamics.py` as a real 6-DOF integrator.
2. Validate against the trade study numbers in the research paper.
3. Run Monte Carlo sweeps and document deviations from nominal.

## Watch for

- Don't conflate Manna with Gryphon. Manna is unmanned cargo — different G profile, different rail use.
- Don't over-engineer Manna-H. It's deliberately the dumbest of the three.
- Manna-B's cost per kg is high — that's correct, that's the design intent. Don't optimize it down.
MDEOF

